      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear-elastic isotropic material model and large-displacement contact formulation are physically appropriate for titanium alloy pedicle screw constructs loaded below ultimate strength under quasi-static conditions.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V exhibits linear-elastic behavior below yield; all predicted peak stresses remain below 0.2% offset yield strength (895 MPa). Large-displacement formulation captures geometric nonlinearity at 40 mm displacement. Model form is appropriate for the COU; no plasticity model required for the pre-yield QoIs assessed."
