      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios; at minimum two load levels or configurations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed at a single load configuration (ASTM F1717 standard compression-bending geometry, 10 mm offset). Only one test condition evaluated; multi-condition coverage not achieved. Achieved level (2) is below required level (3). This gap is acknowledged and accepted given that F1717 is the regulatory standard configuration and the single condition is the most clinically relevant."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
