      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical risk drivers identified in the risk assessment and are the same outputs used in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load transfer to adjacent vertebrae; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are the regulatory acceptance criteria in FDA guidance for spinal implant bench testing. All three QoIs are directly traceable to clinical failure modes (fatigue fracture, acute overload) and are the outputs submitted to FDA."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
