    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 specifies a single standard configuration that constitutes the regulatory benchmark, and the three QoIs all satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). Overall credibility is sufficient to support use of the FEA model ensemble for the stated COU at Medium assurance level.",
